<TITLE> Don't buy textbooks from market: Nahid </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 23 (bdnews24.com)  Education minister Nurul Islam Nahid on Wednesday asked students not to buy primary and secondary textbooks from markets, which will be available free of cost at schools. A group of dishonest businessmen are selling textbooks of 2010 session spreading rumour that they will not be available. The education ministry went to the market but did not find any new textbook on sale. Nahid said: "Action will be taken against those involved in spreading the rumour." The minister reiterated his assurance that students will get textbooks in time. The Upazila education officers have been assigned to coordinate the distribution process, he said adding if there is any problem regarding distribution they will address the problem themselves. bd
